-- CIBC Hires Wildi From Merrill Lynch as Head of Capital Markets in Europe
-- Doug Alexander
-- 2010-07-20T14:13:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/cibc-hires-wildi-from-merrill-lynch-as-head-of-capital-markets-in-europe.html

          
          
             CIBC World Markets  said it hired
 Karl Wildi  from Bank of America Merrill Lynch as a managing
director and head of capital markets in Europe.  
 Wildi will start Sept. 7 in London, Toronto-based CIBC said
in internal memo today. He has more than 20 years of capital
markets experience, including Canadian head of fixed income,
currencies and commodities for Bank of America Merrill Lynch in
Toronto.  
 CIBC also hired  Michael Chiun  from Bank for International
Settlements in Switzerland as an executive director based in
Hong Kong with the firm’s financial solutions group. CIBC hired
 Josh Kay , who comes from Morgan Stanley in London, for the
financial solutions unit in Toronto.  
 CIBC is a unit of Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, the
country’s fifth-biggest bank.  
